Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2024. Jun 22, Trastuzumab.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Ellis CR, Azmat CE. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2023. Nov 12, Adalimumab.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Patel P, King N, Jacobs TF. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2025. Oct 21, Pegfilgrastim.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Aghedo BO, Gupta V. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2023. Jul 3, Filgrastim.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Aboobacker S, Patel P, Al Aboud AM. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2025. Jul 6, Infliximab-abda.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Fatima R, Bittar K, Aziz M. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2024. Mar 21, Infliximab.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Hanif N, Anwer F. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2024. Feb 28, Rituximab.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Cunningham AM, Freeman AM. StatPearls [Internet] StatPearls Publishing; Treasure Island (FL): 2022. Dec 28, Glargine Insulin.</Citation></Reference><Reference><Citation>Pineda C, Casta&#xf1;eda Hern&#xe1;ndez G, Jacobs IA, Alvarez DF, Carini C. Assessing the Immunogenicity of Biopharmaceuticals. BioDrugs. 2016 Jun;30(3):195-206.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pmc">PMC4875071</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">27097915</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Barbosa MD. Immunogenicity of biotherapeutics in the context of developing biosimilars and biobetters. Drug Discov Today. 2011 Apr;16(7-8):345-53.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">21300174</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Singh SC, Bagnato KM. The economic implications of biosimilars. Am J Manag Care. 2015 Dec;21(16 Suppl):s331-40.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">26788809</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Leber MB. Optimizing use and addressing challenges to uptake of biosimilars. Am J Manag Care. 2018 Nov;24(21 Suppl):S457-S461.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">30452214</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Lucio S. The complexities of biosimilars and the regulatory approval process. Am J Manag Care. 2018 Jun;24(11 Suppl):S231-S236.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">29957908</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Schiestl M, Zabransky M, S&#xf6;rgel F. Ten years of biosimilars in Europe: development and evolution of the regulatory pathways. Drug Des Devel Ther. 2017;11:1509-1515.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pmc">PMC5440034</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">28553082</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference><Reference><Citation>Stevenson JG. Clinical data and regulatory issues of biosimilar products. Am J Manag Care. 2015 Dec;21(16 Suppl):s320-30.</Citation><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">26788808</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></Reference></ReferenceList></BookDocument><PubmedBookData><History><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="entrez"><Year>2023</Year><Month>8</Month><Day>28</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="medline"><Year>2023</Year><Month>8</Month><Day>28</Day></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="pubmed"><Year>2023</Year><Month>8</Month><Day>28</Day></PubMedPubDate></History><PublicationStatus>ppublish</PublicationStatus><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">34662086</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></PubmedBookData></PubmedBookArticle><PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">37479945</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2023</Year><Month>08</Month><Day>21</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2023</Year><Month>08</Month><Day>23</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1179-6901</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>23</Volume><Issue>3</Issue><PubDate><Year>2023</Year><Month>Sep</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Drugs in R&amp;D</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Drugs R D</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Physicochemical and Functional Similarity Assessment Between Proposed Bevacizumab Biosimilar BAT1706 and Reference Bevacizumab.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>267</StartPage><EndPage>288</EndPage><MedlinePgn>267-288</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1007/s40268-023-00432-8</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText Label="BACKGROUND" NlmCategory="BACKGROUND">BAT1706 is a proposed biosimilar of bevacizumab, a vascular endothelial growth factor A (VEGF-A)-targeting biologic used to treat several different cancers, including metastatic colorectal cancer. A comprehensive physicochemical and functional similarity assessment is a key component of demonstrating biosimilarity between a reference biologic and a proposed biosimilar. Here we report the physicochemical and functional similarity of BAT1706 and reference bevacizumab sourced from both the United States (US-bevacizumab) and the European Union (EU-bevacizumab).</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="METHOD" NlmCategory="METHODS">A large range of product attributes, including primary and higher order structure, post-translational modifications, purity, stability, and potency, were characterized for BAT1706 and EU/US-bevacizumab using sensitive state-of-the-art analytical techniques. Up to 18 lots of US- and 29 lots of EU-bevacizumab, and 10 unique drug substance lots of BAT1706, were assessed.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="RESULT" NlmCategory="RESULTS">BAT1706 was shown to have an identical amino acid sequence and an indistinguishable higher-order structure compared with EU/US-bevacizumab. BAT1706 and EU/US-bevacizumab also exhibited similar post-translational modifications, glycan profiles, and charge variants. Potency, assessed using a wide range of bioassays, was also shown to be comparable between BAT1706 and EU/US-bevacizumab, with statistical equivalence demonstrated for VEGF-A binding and neutralizing activity.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="CONCLUSION" NlmCategory="CONCLUSIONS">Overall, this extensive comparability exercise demonstrated BAT1706 to match EU/US-bevacizumab in terms of all physicochemical and functional attributes assessed.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>&#xa9; 2023. The Author(s).</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y" EqualContrib="Y"><LastName>Cao</LastName><ForeName>Di</ForeName><Initials>D</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Bio-Thera Solutions, Ltd., Floor 5, Building A6, 11 Kai-Yuan Blvd, Huangpu District, Guangzhou, 510530, Guangdong, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y" EqualContrib="Y"><LastName>Deng</LastName><ForeName>Chunping</ForeName><Initials>C</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Bio-Thera Solutions, Ltd., Floor 5, Building A6, 11 Kai-Yuan Blvd, Huangpu District, Guangzhou, 510530, Guangdong, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Wang</LastName><ForeName>Guangying</ForeName><Initials>G</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Bio-Thera Solutions, Ltd., Floor 5, Building A6, 11 Kai-Yuan Blvd, Huangpu District, Guangzhou, 510530, Guangdong, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Mei</LastName><ForeName>Xiong</ForeName><Initials>X</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Bio-Thera Solutions, Ltd., Floor 5, Building A6, 11 Kai-Yuan Blvd, Huangpu District, Guangzhou, 510530, Guangdong, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Xie</LastName><ForeName>Jianhua</ForeName><Initials>J</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Bio-Thera Solutions, Ltd., Floor 5, Building A6, 11 Kai-Yuan Blvd, Huangpu District, Guangzhou, 510530, Guangdong, China.</Affiliation>